GREP

NAME
        grep - print lines matching a pattern

Named after... 
        the 'ed' command - g/re/p (global / regular expression / print)

SYNOPSIS
       grep [options] PATTERN [FILE...]
       grep [options] [-e PATTERN | -f FILE] [FILE...]

USEFULL Options
       -A (After)                       -B (Before)                     -C NUM (Context)
       --colour{=never,=always,=auto,}
       -i, --ignore-case
       -v, --invert-match
       -c, --count                      
       -m NUM, --max-count=NUM
       -n, --line-number
       -e PATTERN, --regexp=PATTERN
       -F, --fixed-strings              -G, --basic-regexp              -E, --extended-regexp           -P, --perl-regexp
       -H, --with-filename              -h, --no-filename
       -L, --files-without-match        -l, --files-with-matches
       -o, --only-matching
       -q, --quiet, --silent
